Open XML Spreadsheet (Excel) Library for Nim.

Types

XlAlignment = object
  horizontal*: Option[string]
  vertical*: Option[string]
  textRotation*: Option[int]
  wrapText*: Option[bool]
  shrinkToFit*: Option[bool]
  indent*: Option[int]
  relativeIndent*: Option[int]
  justifyLastLine*: Option[bool]
  readingOrder*: Option[int]
  verticalText*: Option[bool]

Represent alignment style.

Possible values of horizontal: "general", "left", "center", "right", "fill", "justify", "centerContinuous", "distributed".

Possible values of vertical: "top", "center", "bottom", "justify", "distributed".

Possible values of textRotation: -90..180 or 255 (vertical text).

XlBorder = object
  outline*: Option[bool]
  diagonalUp*: Option[bool]
  diagonalDown*: Option[bool]
  left*: Option[XlSide]
  right*: Option[XlSide]
  top*: Option[XlSide]
  bottom*: Option[XlSide]
  diagonal*: Option[XlSide]
  vertical*: Option[XlSide]
  horizontal*: Option[XlSide]
Represent border style. 
XlCell = ref object of XlStylable
  rc: XlRC
  formula: string
  value: string
  hyperlink: string
  riches: XlRiches
  ct: XlCellType
  readonly: bool
Represent a cell of a sheet. 
XlCol = ref object of XlStylable
  col: int
  width: float
  hidden: bool
Represent a column of a sheet. 
XlCollection = ref object
  sheet: XlSheet
  rcs: HashSet[XlRC]
Represent a collection of cells. 
XlColor = object
  `auto`*: Option[bool]
  rgb*: Option[string]
  theme*: Option[int]
  indexed*: Option[int]
  tint*: Option[float]

Represent a color.

Possible values of rgb: 6 or 8 hexdigits presents RGB or ARGB color.

Possible values of indexed: 0..64 system default color index.

Possible values of tint: -1.0..1.0.

XlError = object of CatchableError
Default error object. 
XlFill = object
  patternFill*: Option[XlPattern]
  gradientFill*: Option[XlGradient]
Represent fill style. 
XlFont = object
  name*: Option[string]
  charset*: Option[int]
  family*: Option[int]
  size*: Option[float]
  bold*: Option[bool]
  italic*: Option[bool]
  strike*: Option[bool]
  underline*: Option[string]
  vertAlign*: Option[string]
  color*: Option[XlColor]
  scheme*: Option[string]

Represent font style.

Possible values of family: 0..14.

Possible values of underline: "", "single", "double", "singleAccounting", "doubleAccounting".

Possible values of vertAlign: "superscript", "subscript", "baseline".

Possible values of scheme: "major", "minor".

XlGradient = object
  gradientType*: Option[string]
  degree*: Option[float]
  left*, right*, top*, bottom*: Option[float]
  stops*: seq[XlColor]

Represent gradient fill style.

Possible values of gradientType: "linear", "path".

XlNumFmt = object
  code*: Option[string]
Represent number format. 
XlPattern = object
  patternType*: Option[string]
  fgColor*: Option[XlColor]
  bgColor*: Option[XlColor]

Represent pattern fill style.

Possible values of patternType: "none", "solid", "mediumGray", "darkGray", "lightGray", "darkHorizontal", "darkVertical", "darkDown", "darkUp", "darkGrid", "darkTrellis", "lightHorizontal", "lightVertical", "lightDown", "lightUp", "lightGrid", "lightTrellis", "gray125", "gray0625".

XlProperties = object
  title*: string
  subject*: string
  creator*: string
  keywords*: string
  description*: string
  lastModifiedBy*: string
  created*: string
  modified*: string
  category*: string
  contentStatus*: string
  application*: string
  manager*: string
  company*: string
Represent workbook properties. 
XlProtection = object
  locked*: Option[bool]
  hidden*: Option[bool]
Represent protection setting. 
XlRange = ref object
  sheet: XlSheet
  first: XlRC
  last: XlRC
  turned: bool
Represent a rectangle range. 
XlRC = tuple[row: int, col: int]
Represent a cell position. 
XlRCRC = tuple[first: XlRC, last: XlRC]
Represent a range. 
XlRiches = seq[XlRich]
Represent rich string styles. 
XlRow = ref object of XlStylable
  row: int
  height: float
  hidden: bool
Represent a row of a sheet. 
XlSheet = ref object
  workbook: XlWorkbook
  obj: XlObject
  name: string
  hidden: bool
  color: XlColor
  protection: XlSheetProtection
  cells: Table[XlRC, XlCell]
  rows: Table[int, XlRow]
  cols: Table[int, XlCol]
  merges: HashSet[XlRCRC]
  rels: XlRels
  first: XlRC
  last: XlRC
Represent a worksheet. 
XlSheetProtection = object
  sheet*: Option[bool]
  objects*: Option[bool]
  scenarios*: Option[bool]
  selectLockedCells*: Option[bool]
  selectUnlockedCells*: Option[bool]
  formatCells*: Option[bool]
  formatColumns*: Option[bool]
  formatRows*: Option[bool]
  insertColumns*: Option[bool]
  insertRows*: Option[bool]
  insertHyperlinks*: Option[bool]
  deleteColumns*: Option[bool]
  deleteRows*: Option[bool]
  sort*: Option[bool]
  autoFilter*: Option[bool]
  pivotTables*: Option[bool]
  password*: Option[string]
Represent sheet protection properties. 
XlSide = object
  style*: Option[string]
  color*: Option[XlColor]

Represent a side of border.

Possible values of style: "dashDot", "dashDotDot", "dashed", "dotted", "double", "hair", "medium", "mediumDashDot", "mediumDashDotDot", "mediumDashed", "slantDashDot", "thick", "thin".

XlStyle = object
  numFmt*: XlNumFmt
  font*: XlFont
  fill*: XlFill
  border*: XlBorder
  alignment*: XlAlignment
  protection*: XlProtection
Represent all styles. 
XlWorkbook = ref object
  contents: Table[string, XlObject]
  sheets: seq[XlSheet]
  sharedStrings: XlSharedStrings
  sharedStyles: XlSharedStyles
  rels: XlRels
  types: XlTypes
  properties: XlProperties
  active: int
  experimental: bool
Represent a workbook.
